$ GNU Build System: prefix
@ prefix

The *prefix* determines under which directory files are installed (`→ development/make/index[make install]`).
The default is → Linux/fhs/usr/local/.

This default can be overwritten with the → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/Autoconf/macros/AC_PREFIX_DEFAULT macro in → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/configure_ac.

When invoking → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/configure[`./configure`], the default or value set with AC_PREFIX_DEFAULT can again be overwritten with:
code {
$ → ./development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/configure --prefix=/path/to/another/directory
code }
